{"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.Basic","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Lean","Mathlib.Util.TermUnsafe","Mathlib.Lean.NameMapAttribute"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L97-L97","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.mathlibLinterAttr","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.mathlibLinterAttr","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L93-L94","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.getLinters","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.getLinters","doc":"Takes a list of names that resolve to declarations of type `linter`,\nand produces a list of linters. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L88-L89","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.getLinter","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.getLinter","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L86-L86","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.NamedLinter.name","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.NamedLinter.name","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L83-L84","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.NamedLinter","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.NamedLinter","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L77-L81","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.Linter","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.Linter","doc":"A linting test for the `#lint` command.\n\n`test` defines a test to perform on every declaration. It should never fail. Returning `none`\nsignifies a passing test. Returning `some msg` reports a failing test with error `msg`.\n\n`noErrorsFound` is the message printed when all tests are negative, and `errorsFound` is printed\nwhen at least one test is positive.\n\nIf `isFast` is false, this test will be omitted from `#lint-`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L53-L64","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.isAutoDecl","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.isAutoDecl","doc":"Returns true if `decl` is an automatically generated declaration.\n\nAlso returns true if `decl` is an internal name or created during macro\nexpansion.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L44-L45","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.shouldBeLinted","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.shouldBeLinted","doc":"Returns true if `decl` should be checked\nusing `linter`, i.e., if there is no `nolint` attribute. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L31-L31","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.nolintAttr","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.nolintAttr","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.lean#L28-L28","name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.nolint","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Lint/Basic.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.nolint","doc":""}]}